owledge and understandings of the environment. Ultimately, Dokis finds that despite Aboriginal involvement, the evaluation of such projects remains rooted in non-local beliefs about the nature of the environment, the commodification of land, and the inevitability of a hydrocarbon-based economy."-cProvided by publisher.  aIssued also in electronic format.  a8 16 28 29 43 5220aMackenzie Gas Project. 0aBearlake IndianszNorthwest TerritoriesxGovernment relations. 0aEnvironmental impact analysiszNorthwest TerritoriesxDecision making. 0aNatural gas pipelinesxEnvironmental aspectszNorthwest Territories. 0aNatural gas pipelinesxSocial aspectszNorthwest Territories. 0aNatural gas pipelinesxPolitical aspectszNorthwest Territories. 0aNatural resourceszNorthwest TerritoriesxManagement. 0aNorthwest TerritoriesxEnvironmental conditions.1 aDokis, Carly A. (Carly Ann), 1978-, author.tWhere the rivers meet.kNature, history, societykNature, history, societyw(CaOONL)20159007240 0aNature, history, society.  aE 99 B376 D64 2015wLCc1i34917001375968d11/27/2015e10/30/2015lON_SHELFmKEYANOn4p$94.05rYsYtBOOKu1/30/2015o.STAFF. Rec'd Jul/15 MW  aE 99 B376 D64 2015wLCc1i31847001280822lON_SHELFmGPRC_GPp$150.00rYsYtBOOKu7/22/2015  aE99 .B376 D64 2015wLCc1i1007787193d2/17/2016e1/31/2016lON_SHELFmGR_MACEWANn5p$95.00rYsYtBOOKu10/14/2015  aE 99 B376 D65 2015wLCc1i0162034865889d4/10/2017e4/10/2017kCHECKEDOUTlON_SHELFmUAHSSn5p$150.00rMsYtBOOKu11/4/2015zCOUTTS_ADD  aE 99 B376 D65 2015wLCc1i0162034868602d1/28/2017e1/28/2017kCHECKEDOUTlON_SHELFmUAAUGn6p$150.00rMsYtBOOKu11/4/2015zCOUTTS_ADD  aE 99 B376 D64 2015wLCc1i38288001129979lON_SHELFmLAKELND_LLp$150.00rYsYtBOOKu6/10/201601ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no2015122866bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/315171569